I have completed the end-to-end backend implementation of **Milestone 7 (M7)**. Here is a summary of the accomplishments:

### 1. Architectural Changes & State Transitions
- Updated the pipeline workflow in `services/api/app/workflow/pipeline.py` to automatically request `CREATE_DRAFT_PR` approval when verification checks pass (and risk does not block).
- Implemented `apply_pr_approval` inside the pipeline to orchestrate transition pathways:
  - **Approval**: `CREATING_PR` $\rightarrow$ `PR_READY` $\rightarrow$ `RESOLUTION_DRAFTED`
  - **Rejection**: Transitions back to `REVIEW_READY` safely without making any external writes.
  - **Failures**: Transitions to `EXTERNAL_ACTION_FAILED` with retry/renew paths.
- Configured dynamic generation of audience-specific stakeholder updates (3 lines) and technical updates (5 lines) in the incident route and pipeline.
- Implemented automatic generation and persistence of strict postmortems, including summarized timelines and follow-up action items with owner placeholders.

### 2. Provider Integration & Idempotency
- Built the `GitHubPullRequestProvider` (using only standard libraries) to create draft PRs live when a GitHub token is configured.
- Embedded token-redaction and safe error logging within the GitHub provider to prevent any credential leakage.
- Added deterministic idempotency key checks (mapping to database-stored `external_actions`) to prevent duplicate pull request creation on retries.

### 3. API Routes & Persistence
- Exposed the new endpoints in `services/api/app/api/routes/incidents.py`:
  - `POST /api/v1/incidents/{incident_id}/draft-pr`
  - `GET /api/v1/incidents/{incident_id}/draft-pr`
  - `GET /api/v1/incidents/{incident_id}/communications`
  - `POST /api/v1/incidents/{incident_id}/communications/regenerate`
  - `GET /api/v1/incidents/{incident_id}/postmortem`
- Updated mappings in `approvals.py` to route `CREATE_DRAFT_PR` approval decisions directly to the workflow pipeline.

### 4. Verification and Validation Gates
- **Tests**: Created a new test suite at [test_m7_pr_communications.py](file:///D:/Work/Codex/Hackathon%20Projects/OpenAI%20Hackathon/.agent-worktrees/incident-m7-resolution-backend/services/api/tests/test_m7_pr_communications.py). The entire Pytest test suite (136 tests) is **passing 100%**.
- **Static Types**: `mypy --strict` passes with **no issues found**.
- **Linter**: `ruff check` passes with **no issues found**.

### 5. Documentation
